==English==
===Etymology===
There was an attempt at an actual bush festival in [[w:Sydney|Sydney]] in 1919, the idea apparently then extended to the present figurative use.  (Reference: ABC News below.)
===Noun===
'''[[bush]] [[week]]'''
# {{AU}} {{colloquial}} An imaginary or symbolic time when simple people from the [[bush]] (ie. country areas) come to the city, likely to be preyed on by tricksters there.  A question like ''What is this &ndash; bush week?'' is thus a protest by the speaker against some obvious prank or ruse.  (Reference: [[w:Australian Broadcasting Commission|Australian Broadcasting Commission]] News Radio article [http://www.abc.net.au/newsradio/txt/s1512909.htm].)